The paper deals with the problem of multiple measurement vector (MMV) and its identification using compressive sensing (CS) and array signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of CS. The paper also involves sparse signal processing, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing), and array signal processing, which falls under cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm using a large system MMV model, which falls under cs.MM (Mathematical Methods). Finally, the paper proposes a novel generalized MUSIC criterion, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
